Red Team Cheat Sheet

1. Payload Mutation

event.payload += b"_corrupt"


2. Bad Signature

event.signature = os.urandom(64)


3. Parent Drift

event.parent_id = random.randint(0, event.id - 5)


4. Timestamp Attack

event.timestamp += random.randint(-500, 500)


5. Slow-Drip Misbehavior

if random.random() < 0.1: event = corrupt(event)


6. Replay / Stolen Parent

event.parent_id = random.choice(honest_ids)


7. Fake Commit (payload mismatch)

event.payload_commit = blake2b(b"fake").digest()


8. Full Chaos (fuzz)

event.payload = os.urandom(len(event.payload))
event.signature = os.urandom(64)
event.parent_id = random.randint(0, event.id)


Add new attackers:

class MyAttacker(AttackerBase):
    def misbehave(self, event): ...


####Useful Tips for Red-Teaming
✔ Increase simulation length
Longer runs expose drift attacks.

✔ Mix 3–5 attacker types at once
Real adversaries don’t coordinate; chaos reveals more.

✔ Vary attacker density
Try:

1 attacker

2 attackers

50% attackers

attacker majority

You’ll get totally different graph dynamics.

✔ Run random-seed tests
This reveals worst-case paths.
